<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-11T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-11T02:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                                Indonesia/12–1148: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Batavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Livengood</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d408fn1">Repeated in telegram 622, December
                                    13, 8 p. m., to The Hague.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                                    </gloss>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Batavia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-11T15:00:00+08:00">December 11, 1948—3 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1082. <gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 479. Following text
                                Netherlands Delegation letter 3824 dated December 11 from Schuurman
                                to <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> handed by Schuurman <pb facs="0563" n="549" xml:id="pg_549"/> to Cochran noon December
                                11: [Here follows text printed in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>,
                                    <hi rend="italic">3rd yr., Suppl</hi>. (Dec.), page 150.]</p>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> drafting its telegraphic report
                                to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> with which foregoing will be
                                    included.<note n="2" xml:id="d408fn2">The report was transmitted
                                    in telegram 1083, December 12, from Batavia (<gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 480); for text, see <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">3rd yr.,
                                        Suppl</hi>. (Dec.), p. 122.</note> Will report exact hour
                                sent which will be not later than December 13. Signed Cochran.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Livengood</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>